The paper deals with a machine learning problem of maximizing AUC performance, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for adaptive online AUC maximization, which is a subfield of online learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories are closely related to the problem addressed in the paper. Additionally, the paper also deals with high-dimensional sparse data and addresses sparsity in the solution, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
